SECTION 4: ESCAPE VELOCITY AS SOLITON EXCITATION ENERGY
----------------------------------------------------------------------

  To leave a soliton's ground state permanently, you need
  kinetic energy ≥ |binding energy|. The escape velocity
  is the minimum speed for this excitation.

  Soliton                       v_escape        v²/c²      v_esc/c
  ------------------------- ------------ ------------ ------------
  Earth surface             1.119e+4 m/s      1.39e-9     3.731e-5
  Moon surface                2375.0 m/s     6.28e-11     7.923e-6
  Sun surface               6.178e+5 m/s      4.25e-6     0.002061
  Sun at Earth orbit        4.213e+4 m/s      1.97e-8    0.0001405
  Galaxy at Sun             6.146e+5 m/s       4.2e-6      0.00205

  INTERPRETATION: v_escape is the energy needed to leave
  the soliton's potential well. v²/c² is the coupling strength.

  Your jump (~1 m/s) vs Earth escape (11,186 m/s):
  you are in a DEEPLY BOUND ground state. Your jump barely
  perturbs the ground state. You return immediately.
    Jump energy / escape energy            7.192715448e-8
  A jump uses 7.2e-08 of the energy needed to escape.
  You are 10⁷× too slow to leave this soliton.
  [PASS] Jump energy << escape energy
        ratio = 7.19e-8

SECTION 5: CIRCULAR ORBITS AND R₂
----------------------------------------------------------------------

  A circular orbit is the ground state of a two-body soliton.
  The orbital cross-section is R₂ × d² where d = 2r (diameter).
  Angular momentum conservation gives the orbit: L = mvr.
  The orbit IS the minimum-energy bound state for given L.

  Orbit                       Radius (m) Area R₂×(2r)² (m²)
  ------------------------- ------------ ----------------
  Moon orbit                     3.84e+8        4.642e+17
  Earth orbit                    1.5e+11        7.031e+22
  Jupiter orbit                 7.79e+11        1.904e+24
  Neptune orbit                  4.5e+12        6.348e+25
  Sun galactic orbit            2.53e+20        2.012e+41

  Every orbital area = 4R₂ × r² = π × r².
  R₂ is the same geometric conversion in orbits as in
  pipes (Q = R₂d²v), wires (R = ρL/(R₂d²)), and discs.
  The orbit is another R₂ domain — the same geometry
  documented in phys24_domain_lib.py across 15+ domains.
  [PASS] Orbital area via domain_area matches 4R₂r²
        expected: 7.0309346242e+22
        got:      7.0309346242e+22
        digits:   EXACT (need 10)

SECTION 6: COUPLING STRENGTH AT EVERY LEVEL
----------------------------------------------------------------------

  The gravitational coupling GM/(rc²) is the analog of
  alpha = e²/(4πε₀ℏc) = 1/137 for electromagnetism.

  Level                            GM/(rc²)  = v²_esc/(2c²)
  ------------------------- --------------- ---------------
  Earth surface                   6.961e-10       6.961e-10
  Earth-Moon orbit                1.154e-11       1.154e-11
  Sun-Earth orbit                  9.873e-9        9.873e-9
  Sun surface                      2.123e-6        2.123e-6
  Neutron star                        0.376           0.376
  Sun-Galaxy                       2.101e-6        2.101e-6
  Galaxy edge                      1.149e-6        1.149e-6

  PATTERN: GM/(rc²) is the soliton's coupling strength.
  It determines:
    - How deep the ground state is
    - How much energy to escape (v_esc² = 2GM/r)
    - How much spacetime curvature (GR correction ~ GM/(rc²))
    - How relativistic the soliton is

    α_EM                                   0.0072973525643
    α_grav (Earth surface)                 6.9607652964e-10
    α_EM / α_grav                          10483549.227

  The electromagnetic coupling is 1.05e+7× stronger than
  Earth's gravitational coupling. This ratio is why
  the EM soliton boundary (your shoes on the ground)
  holds you up against the gravitational ground state.

SECTION 7: THE NORMAL FORCE — EM SOLITON BOUNDARY
----------------------------------------------------------------------

  You do not fall through the floor because the
  electromagnetic soliton boundary between your atoms
  and the ground's atoms provides the normal force.

  This is a SOLITON BOUNDARY EFFECT (R5):
    Inside your shoe atoms: electron cloud in ground state
    Inside floor atoms: electron cloud in ground state
    At the boundary: Pauli exclusion + EM repulsion
    The boundary force = the normal force

    g (Earth surface, m/s²)                9.8195320328
    F_gravity on human (N)                 687.3672423
    F_normal (= F_gravity at ground state) 687.3672423
    F_EM (single atom pair at 1Å)          2.3066178144e-8
    Atom pairs needed for normal force     29799789025.0
    Contact atoms (shoe, ~200 cm²)         2.0e+17
    Needed / available                     1.4899894512e-7

  Each contact atom contributes ~2.31e-8 N.
  Only ~1.49e-7 of the contact atoms are needed.
  The EM boundary is VASTLY stronger than needed —
  the floor supports you with negligible effort.
  This is because α_EM / α_grav ~ 1.05e+7.
  [PASS] EM force >> gravitational at atomic scale
        EM per atom = 2.31e-8 N vs gravity per atom = 3.44e-15 N

