SECTION 9: GEOLOGICAL NESTING
----------------------------------------------------------------------

  Every layer under your feet is a soliton at its ground
  state within the containing layer.

  Layer                 Top (m) Bottom (m)  ρ (kg/m³)  P (GPa) State
  ------------------ ---------- ---------- ---------- -------- ---------------
  Topsoil                   0.0        1.0     1500.0  7.36e-6 granular, EM-bonded
  Sedimentary rock          1.0     5000.0     2500.0   0.0614 compacted, cemented
  Upper crust            5000.0     2.0e+4     2700.0    0.331 granite/gneiss
  Lower crust            2.0e+4     3.5e+4     3000.0     0.81 basalt/granulite
  Upper mantle           3.5e+4     6.7e+5     3400.0     11.8 olivine, solid
  Lower mantle           6.7e+5    2.89e+6     4500.0     78.7 perovskite, solid
  Outer core            2.89e+6    5.15e+6     1.0e+4    395.0 liquid iron
  Inner core            5.15e+6   6.371e+6     1.3e+4    735.0 solid iron, HCP

  Each layer is at its ground state:
    - Density increases with depth (heavier sinks)
    - Pressure increases with depth (weight of above layers)
    - Phase transitions at boundaries (solid → liquid at outer core)
    - Each boundary is a soliton boundary where the state changes

  The inner core crystallized from the liquid outer core
  as the Earth cooled. It found its ground state: solid HCP iron
  at 330 GPa. This is a PHASE TRANSITION soliton boundary —
  the same structural element as the confinement wall in QCD
  or the electroweak symmetry breaking threshold.
  [PASS] 8 geological layers cataloged
        count = 8

SECTION 10: THE a₀ CONNECTION
